Definition.WordDefinition:
Duds \Duds\, n. pl. [Scot. dud rag, pl. duds clothing of inferior quality.] 1. Old or inferior clothes; tattered garments. [Colloq.] [1913 Webster]
2. Effects, in general.[Slang] [1913 Webster]
duds n : informal terms for clothing [syn: {togs}, {threads}]
